E(X_1X_3)=P(X_1=1,X_3=1)
f(X_1, X_3)
f(X_1, X_3) = X_1 X_3
x_1 = x_3 =1
 E[f(X_1, X_3)] = \sum_{x_1, x_3} f(x_1, x_3) \cdot P(X_1 = x_1, X_3 = x_3). 
 E[X_1X_3 ] = \sum_{x_1 = 0}^{1} \sum_{x_3=0}^{1} x_1x_3 \cdot P(X_1 = x_1, X_3 = x_3). 
 E[f(X_1, X_3)] = P(X_1 = 1, X_3 = 1). \quad \diamond 
